The paper deals with the problem of dense subgraph discovery, which is a fundamental problem in graph mining. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The paper also uses robust optimization theory to address uncertainty in edge weights, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents computational experiments, indicating that it could also belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category.
